> ) / `var'[_n-1]
  3.                 bysort id_store (year): gen logdiff_`var' = ln(`var'[_n]) - ln(`va
> r'[_n-1])
  4.         }

>  depsumbr[_n-1]

> n-1]

. *********************************************************************************
. /* main regression models (DiD) with Year + Id_Store FE structures */
. *********************************************************************************    
>    
.         
.         use "$datadir/temp_annual_dep_traffic", clear

.         
. * simple linear regression models based on raw foot traffic
.         * output regression tables with log traffic on log deposits
. foreach y of varlist depsumbr logdepsumbr deltadepsumbr depsumbr_w logdepsumbr_w delt
> adepsumbr_w {
  2.         foreach var of varlist devices_store devices_plot devices_store_or_plot dw
> elled_store dwelled_plot dwelled_store_or_plot employees traffic_store traffic_plot t
> raffic_store_or_plot tf_dwelled_store tf_dwelled_plot tf_dwelled_store_or_plot tf_emp
> loyees {
  3.                 if "`var'" == "devices_store" {
  4.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(year id_store) 
  5.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_raw.xl
> s", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y'") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) replace ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Year FE, Yes)   
  6.                 }
  7.                 else {
  8.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(year id_store) 
  9.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_raw.xl
> s", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y'") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) append ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Year FE, Yes)
 10.                 }
 11.         }
 12.         * add clustering by state
.         foreach var of varlist devices_store devices_plot devices_store_or_plot dwell
> ed_store dwelled_plot dwelled_store_or_plot employees traffic_store traffic_plot traf
> fic_store_or_plot tf_dwelled_store tf_dwelled_plot tf_dwelled_store_or_plot tf_employ
> ees {
 13.                 if "`var'" == "devices_store" {
 14.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(year id_store) vce(cl stnumb)
 15.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_raw_cl
> st.xls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y'") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) replace ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Year FE, Yes, Note: standard errors c
> lustering at state level)  
 16.                 }
 17.                 else {
 18.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(year id_store) vce(cl stnumb)
 19.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_raw_cl
> st.xls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y'") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) append ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Year FE, Yes, Note: standard errors c
> lustering at state level)
 20.                 }
 21.         }
 22.         * add clustering by county
.         foreach var of varlist devices_store devices_plot devices_store_or_plot dwell
> ed_store dwelled_plot dwelled_store_or_plot employees traffic_store traffic_plot traf
> fic_store_or_plot tf_dwelled_store tf_dwelled_plot tf_dwelled_store_or_plot tf_employ
> ees {
 23.                 if "`var'" == "devices_store" {
 24.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(year id_store) vce(cl cntynumb)
 25.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_raw_cl
> cnty.xls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y'") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) replace ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Year FE, Yes, Note: standard errors c
> lustering at county level) 
 26.                 }
 27.                 else {
 28.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(year id_store) vce(cl cntynumb)
 29.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_raw_cl
> cnty.xls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y'") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) append ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Year FE, Yes, Note: standard errors c
> lustering at county level)
 30.                 }
 31.         }
 32.         * add clustering by zip 
.         foreach var of varlist devices_store devices_plot devices_store_or_plot dwell
> ed_store dwelled_plot dwelled_store_or_plot employees traffic_store traffic_plot traf
> fic_store_or_plot tf_dwelled_store tf_dwelled_plot tf_dwelled_store_or_plot tf_employ
> ees {
 33.                 if "`var'" == "devices_store" {
 34.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(year id_store) vce(cl zipbr)
 35.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_raw_cl
> zip.xls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y'") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) replace ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Year FE, Yes, Note: standard errors c
> lustering at zip level)    
 36.                 }
 37.                 else {
 38.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(year id_store) vce(cl zipbr)
 39.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_raw_cl
> zip.xls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y'") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) append ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Year FE, Yes, Note: standard errors c
> lustering at zip level)
 40.                 }
 41.         }
 42. }

dir : seeout

. 
. * simple linear regression models based on (growth rates of traffic)
.         * output regression tables with period-on-period percentage change of traffic
>  and log deposits
. foreach y of varlist depsumbr logdepsumbr deltadepsumbr depsumbr_w logdepsumbr_w delt
> adepsumbr_w {
  2.         foreach var of varlist delta_* {
  3.                 if "`var'" == "delta_devices_store" {
  4.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(year id_store) 
  5.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model.xls", 
> /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) replace ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Year FE, Yes)   
  6.                 }
  7.                 else {
  8.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(year id_store) 
  9.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model.xls", 
> /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) append ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Year FE, Yes)
 10.                 }
 11.         }
 12.         * add clustering by state
.         foreach var of varlist delta_* {
 13.                 if "`var'" == "delta_devices_store" {
 14.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(year id_store) vce(cl stnumb)
 15.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_clst.x
> ls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) replace ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Year FE, Yes, Note: standard errors c
> lustering at state level)  
 16.                 }
 17.                 else {
 18.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(year id_store) vce(cl stnumb)
 19.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_clst.x
> ls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) append ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Year FE, Yes, Note: standard errors c
> lustering at state level)
 20.                 }
 21.         }
 22.         * add clustering by county
.         foreach var of varlist delta_* {
 23.                 if "`var'" == "delta_devices_store" {
 24.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(year id_store) vce(cl cntynumb)
 25.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_clcnty
> .xls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) replace ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Year FE, Yes, Note: standard errors c
> lustering at county level) 
 26.                 }
 27.                 else {
 28.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(year id_store) vce(cl cntynumb)
 29.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_clcnty
> .xls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) append ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Year FE, Yes, Note: standard errors c
> lustering at county level)
 30.                 }
 31.         }
 32.         * add clustering by zip 
.         foreach var of varlist delta_* {
 33.                 if "`var'" == "delta_devices_store" {
 34.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(year id_store) vce(cl zipbr)
 35.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_clzip.
> xls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) replace ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Year FE, Yes, Note: standard errors c
> lustering at zip level)    
 36.                 }
 37.                 else {
 38.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(year id_store) vce(cl zipbr)
 39.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_clzip.
> xls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) append ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Year FE, Yes, Note: standard errors c
> lustering at zip level)
 40.                 }
 41.         }
 42. }

dir : seeout

.         
. * output regression tables with log-diff of traffic and deposits
. 
. foreach y of varlist logdiffdepsumbr logdiffdepsumbr_w {
  2.         foreach var of varlist logdiff_* {
  3.                 if "`var'" == "logdiff_devices_store" {
  4.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(year id_store) 
  5.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model.xls", 
> /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) replace ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Year FE, Yes)   
  6.                 }
  7.                 else {
  8.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(year id_store) 
  9.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model.xls", 
> /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) append ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Year FE, Yes)
 10.                 }
 11.         }
 12.         * add clustering by state
.         foreach var of varlist logdiff_* {
 13.                 if "`var'" == "logdiff_devices_store" {
 14.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(year id_store) vce(cl stnumb)
 15.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_clst.x
> ls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) replace ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Year FE, Yes, Note: standard errors c
> lustering at state level)  
 16.                 }
 17.                 else {
 18.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(year id_store) vce(cl stnumb)
 19.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_clst.x
> ls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(2) append ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Year FE, Yes, Note: standard errors c
> lustering at state level)
 20.                 }
 21.         }
 22.         * add clustering by county
.         foreach var of varlist logdiff_* {
 23.                 if "`var'" == "logdiff_devices_store" {
 24.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(year id_store) vce(cl cntynumb)
 25.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_clcnty
> .xls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) replace ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Year FE, Yes, Note: standard errors c
> lustering at county level) 
 26.                 }
 27.                 else {
 28.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(year id_store) vce(cl cntynumb)
 29.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_clcnty
> .xls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) append ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Year FE, Yes, Note: standard errors c
> lustering at county level)
 30.                 }
 31.         }
 32.         * add clustering by zip 
.         foreach var of varlist logdiff_* {
 33.                 if "`var'" == "logdiff_devices_store" {
 34.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(year id_store) vce(cl zipbr)
 35.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_clzip.
> xls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) replace ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Year FE, Yes, Note: standard errors c
> lustering at zip level)    
 36.                 }
 37.                 else {
 38.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(year id_store) vce(cl zipbr)
 39.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_clzip.
> xls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) append ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Year FE, Yes, Note: standard errors c
> lustering at zip level)
 40.                 }
 41.         }
 42. }

. 
. *********************************************************************************
. /*same regression models but with stateXyear or countyXyear FE and branch FE structur
> es (using only winsorized deposits)*/
. *********************************************************************************
. 
. use "$datadir/temp_annual_dep_traffic", clear

. 
. * generate state year fe structure
. egen state_year_fe = group(stalpbr year)

. egen county_year_fe = group(cntynumb year)

. 
. *** County X Year FEs
. * log diff models with countyXyear FEs
. foreach y of varlist logdiffdepsumbr_w {
  2.         * clustering by zip
.         foreach var of varlist logdiff_* {
  3.                 if "`var'" == "logdiff_devices_store" {
  4.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(county_year_fe id_store) vce(cl 
> zipbr)
  5.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_cntyyr
> .xls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) replace ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, CountyXYear FE, Yes)    
  6.                 }
  7.                 else {
  8.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(county_year_fe id_store) vce(cl 
> zipbr)
  9.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_cntyyr
> .xls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) append ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, CountyXYear FE, Yes)
 10.                 }
 11.         }
 12. }

> fic_store_or_plot tf_dwelled_store tf_dwelled_plot tf_dwelled_store_or_plot tf_employ

  3.                 if "`var'" == "logdiff_devices_store" {
  4.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(county_year_fe id_store) vce(cl 
> zipbr)
  5.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_cntyyr
> .xls", ///

>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) replace ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, CountyXYear FE, Yes)

. 
. *** State X Year FEs
. * again, log diff models with winsorized deposits and traffic measures as wellas bran
> ch and stateXyear FEs 
. foreach y of varlist logdiffdepsumbr_w {
  2.         foreach var of varlist logdiff_* {
  3.                 if "`var'" == "logdiff_devices_store" {
  4.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(state_year_fe id_store) 
  5.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_styr.x
> ls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) replace ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, StateXYear FE, Yes)     
  6.                 }
  7.                 else {
  8.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(state_year_fe id_store) 
  9.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_styr.x
> ls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) append ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, StateXYear FE, Yes)
 10.                 }
 11.         }
 12.         * add clustering by state
.         foreach var of varlist logdiff_* {
 13.                 if "`var'" == "logdiff_devices_store" {
 14.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(state_year_fe id_store) vce(cl s
> tnumb)
 15.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_styr_c
> lst.xls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) replace ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, StateXYear FE, Yes, Note: standard er
> rors clustering at state level)    
 16.                 }
 17.                 else {
 18.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(state_year_fe id_store) vce(cl s
> tnumb)
 19.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_styr_c
> lst.xls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(2) append ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, StateXYear FE, Yes, Note: standard er
> rors clustering at state level)
 20.                 }
 21.         }
 22.         * add clustering by county
.         foreach var of varlist logdiff_* {
 23.                 if "`var'" == "logdiff_devices_store" {
 24.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(state_year_fe id_store) vce(cl c
> ntynumb)
 25.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_styr_c
> lcnty.xls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) replace ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, StateXYear FE, Yes, Note: standard er
> rors clustering at county level)   
 26.                 }
 27.                 else {
 28.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(state_year_fe id_store) vce(cl c
> ntynumb)
 29.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_styr_c
> lcnty.xls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) append ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, StateXYear FE, Yes, Note: standard er
> rors clustering at county level)
 30.                 }
 31.         }
 32.         * add clustering by zip 
.         foreach var of varlist logdiff_* {
 33.                 if "`var'" == "logdiff_devices_store" {
 34.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(state_year_fe id_store) vce(cl z
> ipbr)
 35.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_styr_c
> lzip.xls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) replace ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, StateXYear FE, Yes, Note: standard er
> rors clustering at zip level)      
 36.                 }
 37.                 else {
 38.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(state_year_fe id_store) vce(cl z
> ipbr)
 39.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_styr_c
> lzip.xls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) append ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, StateXYear FE, Yes, Note: standard er
> rors clustering at zip level)
 40.                 }
 41.         }
 42. }

. 
. * also output the raw associations between deposits and traffic changes using stateXy
> ear FEs 
. * only check the raw and logged deposits (after winsorization) this time
. foreach y of varlist depsumbr_w logdepsumbr_w {
  2.         foreach var of varlist delta_* {
  3.                 if "`var'" == "delta_devices_store" {
  4.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(state_year_fe id_store) 
  5.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_styr.x
> ls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) replace ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, StateXYear FE, Yes)     
  6.                 }
  7.                 else {
  8.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(state_year_fe id_store) 
  9.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_styr.x
> ls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) append ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, StateXYear FE, Yes)
 10.                 }
 11.         }
 12.         * add clustering by state
.         foreach var of varlist delta_* {
 13.                 if "`var'" == "delta_devices_store" {
 14.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(state_year_fe id_store) vce(cl s
> tnumb)
 15.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_clst.x
> ls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) replace ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, StateXYear FE, Yes, Note: standard er
> rors clustering at state level)    
 16.                 }
 17.                 else {
 18.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(state_year_fe id_store) vce(cl s
> tnumb)
 19.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_styr_c
> lst.xls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) append ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, StateXYear FE, Yes, Note: standard er
> rors clustering at state level)
 20.                 }
 21.         }
 22.         * add clustering by county
.         foreach var of varlist delta_* {
 23.                 if "`var'" == "delta_devices_store" {
 24.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(state_year_fe id_store) vce(cl c
> ntynumb)
 25.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_styr_c
> lcnty.xls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) replace ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, StateXYear FE, Yes, Note: standard er
> rors clustering at county level)   
 26.                 }
 27.                 else {
 28.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(state_year_fe id_store) vce(cl c
> ntynumb)
 29.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_styr_c
> lcnty.xls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) append ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, StateXYear FE, Yes, Note: standard er
> rors clustering at county level)
 30.                 }
 31.         }
 32.         * add clustering by zip 
.         foreach var of varlist delta_* {
 33.                 if "`var'" == "delta_devices_store" {
 34.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(state_year_fe id_store) vce(cl z
> ipbr)
 35.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_styr_c
> lzip.xls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) replace ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, StateXYear FE, Yes, Note: standard er
> rors clustering at zip level)      
 36.                 }
 37.                 else {
 38.                         reghdfe `y' `var', absorb(state_year_fe id_store) vce(cl z
> ipbr)
 39.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/`y'_traffic_prediction_model_styr_c
> lzip.xls", /// 
>                         title ("Annual Traffic Change on Branch Deposits") ctitle("`y
> '") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) append ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, StateXYear FE, Yes, Note: standard er
> rors clustering at zip level)
 40.                 }
 41.         }
 42. }

(MWFE estimator converged in 8 iterations)

                                                  Prob > F        =     0.0001
                                                  R-squared       =     0.9390
                                                  Adj R-squared   =     0.9217

. 
. /**************
>         Event Study (DiD) w.r.t. Wells Fargo Scandal
>         ***************/        
. 
. *** create closest bank branch pair (wells fargo to other banks) using sod (
. *** but only those uninumbr matched to advan data)
. use "$datadir/source data/SOD/sodupdate2021", clear

. drop if uninumbr == .
(225,118 observations deleted)

. collapse (median) sims_latitude sims_longitude (first) stalpbr, by(uninumbr) //keep s
> tcntybr so that we only compute distances within a county (to minimize computation re
> quired)

. drop if sims_latitude == . | sims_longitude == .
(3,988 observations deleted)

. * merge with advan data so that we don't identify branches not in the advan data set
. merge 1:m uninumbr using "$datadir/cleaned data/weekly_advan_traffic_mergedbanks_upda
> ted20221004", keepusing(id_store)

    Result                      Number of obs
    -----------------------------------------
    Not matched                       111,118
        from master                   111,118  (_merge==1)
        from using                          0  (_merge==2)

    Matched                        11,688,208  (_merge==3)
    -----------------------------------------

. keep if _merge == 3
(111,118 observations deleted)

. drop _merge 

. collapse (median) sims_latitude sims_longitude (first) stalpbr, by(uninumbr)  

. 
. * joinby stcntybr for calculation of distances
. tempfile sod_dist

. save `sod_dist'
file C:\Users\zsong98\AppData\Local\Temp\ST_462c_000003.tmp saved as .dta format

. rename uninumbr key_uninumbr 

. rename (sims_latitude sims_longitude) (key_lat key_long)

. joinby stalpbr using `sod_dist'

>  dwelled_plot dwelled_store_or_plot employees traffic_store traffic_plot traffic_stor
> e_or_plot traffic_employees tf_* {
  2.         if "`var'" == "devices_store" {
  3.                 reghdfe `var' treatedxpost, vce(cl zip) absorb(id_store zip_week) 
  4.                 outreg2 using "$tabdir/twfe_main_zipweek.xls", /// 
>                 title ("TWFE Estimator of Wells Fargo Scandal Effect") ctitle("`var'"
> ) ///
>                 bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) replace ///
>                 addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Week FE, Yes, Note: standard errors clusterin
> g at zip level)    
  5.         }
  6.         else {
  7.                 reghdfe `var' treatedxpost, vce(cl zip) absorb(id_store zip_week) 
  8.                 outreg2 using "$tabdir/twfe_main_zipweek.xls", /// 
>                 title ("TWFE Estimator of Wells Fargo Scandal Effect") ctitle("`var'"
> ) ///
>                 bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) append ///
>                 addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Week FE, Yes, Note: standard errors clusterin
> g at zip level)
  9.         }
 10. }

. *********************************************************************************
. /* pre-post with dwelled traffic using different event windows */
. *********************************************************************************    
>    
. * new from Dec 6th, 2022
. *** dynamic regression tables and event-study plots with different post windows 
. 
. * generate different event window data sets
. forv j = 12(12)48 {
  2.         use "$datadir/temp_weekly_traffic", clear
  3.         * generate dummies relative to wells fargo scandal week
.         forv i = 1/`j' {
  4.                 bysort id_store (id_week): gen event_plus`i'weeks = 1 if id_week -
>  event_week == `i' & treated == 1
  5.         replace event_plus`i'weeks = 0 if event_plus`i'weeks >=.
  6. }
  7. 
.         forv i = 12(-1)1 {
  8.                 bysort id_store (id_week): gen event_minus`i'weeks = 1 if event_we
> ek - id_week == `i' & treated == 1
  9.         replace event_minus`i'weeks = 0 if event_minus`i'weeks >=.
 10. }
 11.         * dynamic regressions
.         * keep only those in the per-post period
.         drop if event_week-id_week > 12 // drop the pre-trends that are more than 12 
> weeks before 
 12.         drop if id_week-event_week > `j' //drop this post-trends that are more tha
> n `i' weeks after
 13.         save "$datadir/temp_weekly_traffic_eventwindow_`j'.dta", replace // save t
> his for later heterogeneity test-16 -> 12 or 24 or 36 or 48
 14. }

. 
. * use different event windows to generate event study plots for dwelled device/traffi
> c and 
. * dwelled device or plot and 
. forv i = 12(12)48 {
  2.         use "$datadir/temp_weekly_traffic_eventwindow_`i'.dta", clear
  3.         foreach var of varlist dwelled_store dwelled_plot dwelled_store_or_plot tf
> _* {
  4.                 if "`var'" == "dwelled_store" {
  5.                         reghdfe `var' event_minus* event_plus*, vce(cl zip) absorb
> (id_store id_week) 
  6.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/twfe_dynamic_dwelled_`i'.xls", /// 
>                         title ("TWFE Estimator of Wells Fargo Scandal Effect") ctitle
> ("`var'") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) replace ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Week FE, Yes, Note: standard errors c
> lustering at zip level)    
  7.                 }
  8.                 else {
  9.                         reghdfe `var' event_minus* event_plus*, vce(cl zip) absorb
> (id_store id_week) 
 10.                         outreg2 using "$tabdir/twfe_dynamic_dwelled_`i'.xls", /// 
>                         title ("TWFE Estimator of Wells Fargo Scandal Effect") ctitle
> ("`var'") ///
>                         bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) append ///
>                         addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Week FE, Yes, Note: standard errors c
> lustering at zip level)
 11.                 }
 12.         }
 13.         foreach var of varlist dwelled_store dwelled_plot dwelled_store_or_plot tf
> _* {
 14.                 if "`var'" == "dwelled_store" {
 15.                         reghdfe `var' event_minus* event_plus*, vce(cl zip) absorb
> (id_store zip_week)

> s", /// 
>                         title ("TWFE Estimator of Wells Fargo Scandal Effect") ctitle
> ("`var'") ///

> lustering at zip level)

. 
. * use different event windows generated above to generate different event study plots
>  
. 
. forv x = 12(12)48 {
  2.         foreach file in twfe_dynamic_dwelled twfe_dynamic_dwelled_zipweek {
  3.         import delimited "$tabdir/twfe_dynamic_dwelled_`x'.txt", clear
  4. 
.         // v2 - dwelled_store; v3 - dwelled_plot; v4 - dwelled_store_or_plot
.         // v5 - tf_dwelled_store; v6 - tf_dwelled_store; v7 - tf_dwelled_store_or_plo
> t
. 
.         * check if the correct numbers are dropped
.         drop in 1/4
  5.         * drop the bottom several lines 
.         drop if v2 == ""
  6.         drop if v1 == "Observations" | v1 == "R-squared"
  7.         drop if v2 == "Yes"
  8.         
.         replace v1 = "se_" +  v1[_n-1] if v1=="" & v1[_n-1]!=""
  9.         forval i = 2/7  {
 10.                 replace v`i' = subinstr(v`i', "]", "",.) 
 11.                 replace v`i' = subinstr(v`i', "[", "",.) 
 12.                 replace v`i' = "" if v`i' == "-" 
 13.                 replace v`i' = subinstr(v`i', "*", "",.) 
 14.         }       
 15. 
.         foreach v of varlist v2-v7 {
 16.                 destring `v', replace
 17.                 replace `v' = 0 if v1 == "Constant"
 18.                 replace `v' = 0 if v1 == "se_Constant"
 19.         }
 20. 
.         egen week = seq(), from(-12) block(2)
 21.         * note that constant is week 0, hence need to shift weeks after event +1
.         replace week = week + 1 if week >= 0
 22.         local d = `x' + 1
 23.         replace week = 0 if week == `d' // make constant to be the event date 
 24.         replace v1 = "event" if v1 == "Constant"
 25.         replace v1 = "se_event" if v1 == "se_Constant"
 26.         replace v1 = substr(v1, 1, 2)
 27.         reshape wide v2-v7, i(week) j(v1) string
 28. 
.         foreach v of numlist 2/7 {
 29.                 rename v`v'ev v`v'coef
 30.                 rename v`v'se v`v'se
 31.                 gen v`v'll = v`v'coef - v`v'se*1.96
 32.                 gen v`v'uu = v`v'coef + v`v'se*1.96
 33.         }
 34. 
.         if "`file'" == "twfe_dynamic_dwelled" local name "week" 
 35.         if "`file'" == "twfe_dynamic_dwelled_zipweek" local name "zipweek" 
 36. 
.         * raw device plots
.         #delimit ;
delimiter now ;
.         twoway
>                 (rcap v2ll v2uu week, lcolor($c1) lw(thin) lp(dash) yaxis(1))        
>                                                                    
>                 (scatter v2coef week, m(o) mcolor($c1) yaxis(1))                     
>                                                                                      
>       
>                 , xlabel(-12(1)`x', val angle(0) labsize(vsmall))
>                 yline(0, lcolor(black)) legend(off)                                  
>                            
>                 xtitle("Weeks")
>                 ytitle("Dwelled Store Devices") $gpr
>                 ylabel(-0.2(0.1)0.2) graphregion(color(white));
 37.         #delimit cr
delimiter now cr
.         graph export "$figdir/dwelled_store_evolution_`name'_`x'.pdf", replace
 38.         #delimit ;
delimiter now ;
.         twoway
>                 (rcap v3ll v3uu week, lcolor($c1) lw(thin) lp(dash) yaxis(1))        
>                                                                    
>                 (scatter v3coef week, m(o) mcolor($c1) yaxis(1))                     
>                                                                                      
>       
>                 , xlabel(-12(1)`x', val angle(0) labsize(vsmall))
>                 yline(0, lcolor(black)) legend(off)                                  
>                            
>                 xtitle("Weeks")
>                 ytitle("Dwelled Plot Devices") $gpr
>                 ylabel(-0.2(0.1)0.2) graphregion(color(white));
 39.         #delimit cr
delimiter now cr
.         graph export "$figdir/dwelled_plot_evolution_`name'_`x'.pdf", replace
 40.         #delimit ;
delimiter now ;
.         twoway
>                 (rcap v4ll v4uu week, lcolor($c1) lw(thin) lp(dash) yaxis(1))        
>                                                                    
>                 (scatter v4coef week, m(o) mcolor($c1) yaxis(1))                     
>                                                                                      
>       
>                 , xlabel(-12(1)`x', val angle(0) labsize(vsmall))
>                 yline(0, lcolor(black)) legend(off)                                  
>                            
>                 xtitle("Weeks")
>                 ytitle("Dwelled Store or Plot Devices") $gpr
>                 ylabel(-0.2(0.1)0.2) graphregion(color(white));
 41.         #delimit cr
delimiter now cr
.         graph export "$figdir/dwelled_store_or_plot_evolution_`name'_`x'.pdf", replac
> e
 42. 
.         * dwelled device plots
.         #delimit ;
delimiter now ;
.         twoway

delimiter now cr
.         graph export "$figdir/tf_dwelled_store_evolution_`name'_`x'.pdf", replace

. foreach var of varlist devices_store devices_plot devices_store_or_plot dwelled_store
>  dwelled_plot dwelled_store_or_plot employees traffic_store traffic_plot traffic_stor
> e_or_plot traffic_employees tf_* {
  2.         if "`var'" == "devices_store" {
  3.                 reghdfe `var' event_minus* event_plus*, vce(cl zip) absorb(id_stor
> e id_week) 
  4.                 outreg2 using "$tabdir/twfe_dynamic.xls", /// 
>                 title ("TWFE Estimator of Wells Fargo Scandal Effect") ctitle("`var'"
> ) ///
>                 bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) replace ///
>                 addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Week FE, Yes, Note: standard errors clusterin
> g at zip level)    
  5.         }
  6.         else {
  7.                 reghdfe `var' event_minus* event_plus*, vce(cl zip) absorb(id_stor
> e id_week) 
  8.                 outreg2 using "$tabdir/twfe_dynamic.xls", /// 
>                 title ("TWFE Estimator of Wells Fargo Scandal Effect") ctitle("`var'"
> ) ///
>                 bracket bdec(4) sdec(4) append ///
>                 addtext(Branch FE, Yes, Week FE, Yes, Note: standard errors clusterin
> g at zip level)
  9.         }
 10. }
